<HTMLTextAreaElementSelect>
<summary>
The <strong><c>select()</c></strong> method of the <see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement"/> interface selects the entire contents of the {{htmlelement("textarea")}} element. In addition, the <see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.Select_event"/> event is fired. The <c>select()</c> method does not take any parameters and does not return a value.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea">textarea</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement/select_event"/> event<br/>-<see cref="EventTarget.AddEventListener"/><br/>-CSS {{cssxref(&amp;quot;::selection&amp;quot;)}} pseudo-element<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTextAreaElement/select"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<returns>None (<see cref="Undefined"/>).</returns>
</HTMLTextAreaElementSelect>
